data.text:
Come off the side lines and into the room to understand what Project 2025 and other policies mean in the US. #YWCASHR is kicking off it’s #GOTV campaign and has assembled a dynamic panel of experts from across the state to delve in and inform our thinking. Stay tuned for more info. #YWCA #YWCASHR #EliminateRacism #EmpowerWomen #YWCAIsOnAMission #YtheW #thePowerisintheW #YWomenVote #EndGBV #TowardEquality #WomenAreVoting

We honor the legacy of Congresswoman Shelia Jackson Lee whose life’s work advocated for and advanced efforts on behalf of women and those pressed against the margins. Thank you for establishing Juneteenth as a federal holiday, ensuring the reauthorization of the Violence Against Women Act (VAWA), and making sure Congress did its part to fight the epidemic of domestic violence and stalking. Our mission lost one of its greatest champions. Rest well Congresswoman - the movement continues! #YWCA #YWCASHR #EliminateRacism #EmpowerWomen #YWCAIsOnAMission #YtheW #thePowerisintheW #EndDomesticViolence #EndGBV

Thank you to our partners at Capital Group for hosting our All Teams Meeting and Portsmouth Economic Development for presenting Portsmouth@Work. What a way to start off our new fiscal year. Today was all about "Empowering Movement Leaders" and focusing on our future through a culture of care! Some great things are about to happen! #757, you're in great hands with @YWCASHR! #CapitalGroup #YWCA #YWCASHR #EliminateRacism #EmpowerWomen #YWCAIsOnAMission #YtheW #thePowerisintheW

Thank you to our partners of the Virginia Beach Alumnae Chapter of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc. for honoring our CEO, Michelle Ellis Young, at your Dr. Dorothy I. Heights Hats Off Scholarship Luncheon. This honor means a lot because of Dr. Heights' longstanding work at YWCA USA - 1944-1977 where she helped move YW toward racial equality in our ranks and established the Center for Racial Justice in 1965. Congrats Michelle for embodying her spirit! #YWCA #YWCASHR #EliminateRacism #EmpowerWomen #YWCAIsOnAMission #YtheW #thePowerisintheW #YWomenVote #TowardEquality #GOTV #WomenAreVoting

We’re throwing it not too far back for #WaybackWednesday. Just last month some of the most talented and dedicated game-changers, world-shakers, do-gooders, activists and more met at Norfolk State University for our Annual Conference on R.E.S.T. ~ We the People. Though the conference is over, the work and legacy continues. Wanna know how you can help? Join and support local organizations like YWCA South Hampton Roads. Here’s some things you can do: Volunteer with us! Follow the link for more details- https://loom.ly/HOSZSig Support our events - Follow us on social media to learn more about our upcoming events Donate - Your contribution helps us fulfill our mission to eliminate racism, empower women and promote peace, justice, dignity and freedom for all. Donate to our shelter - https://loom.ly/EPWVHro Donate to our mission - https://loom.ly/PtXSw10 #RESTNow #YWCAIsOnAMission #TheWMakesADifference #Advocacy

Three of our partners are joining forces to make sure our community is made better. Make sure to register for the 5-week Diabetes Summer Series at Brighton Rock Church in Portsmouth - July 30-August 27 (every Tuesday) with host Arnel Rodriguez, Diabetes Educator, RN and open day speaker, Dr. Newby, Bon Secours Cardiologist. Here's to your health! @BonSecoursHealthSystem @brightonrockamezion #YWCA #YWCASHR #EliminateRacism #EmpowerWomen #YWCAIsOnAMission #YtheW #thePowerisintheW

Passionate about the work of equity and justice and the power of women and girls? Then consider joining our team! YWCA SHR offers many opportunities to feed your soul and help build community. If this speaks to you, then speak with us! Apply now at ywca-shr.org and be on your way to help #EliminateRacism #EmpowerWomen ! #YWCAIsOnAMission #YtheW #thePowerisintheW #wearehiring

Today, our office will be closed as we recognize the 4th of July and the need to still work for justice. We will resume normal business hours remotely on Friday, July 5th. Make sure to drop us a line and tell us what freedom means to you. If you are in crisis and in need of immediate assistance, the Coordinated Crisis Response Hotline can be reached 24/7 at 757-251-0144. #YWCA #YWCASHR #EliminateRacism #EmpowerWomen #YWCAIsOnAMission #YtheW #thePowerisintheW
